==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brontosaurus
<hw>Bron`to*sau"rus</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>bronth`</grk> thunder + <grk>say^ros</grk> lizard.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of large sauropod American dinosaurs
of the jurassic era, or an individual of that genus. A length of sixty
feet is believed to have been attained by these reptiles. The genus is
also called <altname>Apatosaurus</altname>, and individuals of the genus
are also called <altname>brontosaurs</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brontotherium</ent>⟦br⟧
